===Etymology===
From Middle English '''[[percynne]]''' < Middle French '''[[persien]]''' < Latin '''*[[Persianus]]''' < Latin '''[[Persia]]''' < Greek '''[[Περσίς]]''' < Old Persian '''[[Pārsa]]'''.

===Proper noun===
'''Persian''' (''plural:'' [[Persians]])

#A person from [[Persia]] ([[Iran]]).
#A group of very similar languages spoken primarily in Iran, Afghanistan, and Tajikistan, Persian belongs to the Southwestern branch of the [[Iranian]] subfamily of the Indo-Iranian family of languages. Indo-Iranian itself is a subfamily of the Indo-European language family. Closely related languages include [[Kurdish]], [[Pashto]], and [[Avestan]].
#A [[cinnamon]] [[bun]] coated with [[pink]] [[icing]] on top (local [[colloquialism]], ''[http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thunder_Bay%2C_Ontario Thunder Bay, Ontario], [[Canada]]'')
#A breed of [[cat]].

====Usage====
*Persian is the name applied to the official language of Iran. This language is also spoken in Tajikistan and some parts of Afghanistan. Some people use the local name "Farsi" in English to refer to any of the Persian dialects. Afghanis usually call it [[Dari]], and the version spoken in Tajikistan is called Tajik Persian or simply Tajik.

